Datatype.Name: int
Datatype.Description: Sequence of digits without commas or decimals and optional sign character (ASCII characters "-" and "0" - "9" ). The sign character utilizes one byte (i.e. positive int is "99999" while negative int is "-99999"). Note that int values may contain leading zeros (e.g. "00023" = "23"). Examples: 723 in field 21 would be mapped int as |21=723|. -723 in field 12 would be mapped int as |12=-723| The following data types are based on int.

Datatype.Name: float
Datatype.Description: Sequence of digits with optional decimal point and sign character (ASCII characters "-", "0" - "9" and "."); the absence of the decimal point within the string will be interpreted as the float representation of an integer value. All float fields must accommodate up to fifteen significant digits.

Datatype.Name: char
Datatype.Description: Alpha-numeric free format strings, can include any character or punctuation except the delimiter. All char fields are case sensitive.

Datatype.Name: time
Datatype.Description: Time/date combination in YYYYMMDD-HH:MM:SS format, colons and dash required. Valid values: YYYY = 0000-9999, MM = 01-12, DD = 01-31, HH = 00-23, MM = 00-59, SS = 00-59.

Datatype.Name: date
Datatype.Description: Date in YYYYMMDD format. Valid values: YYYY = 0000-9999, MM = 01-12, DD = 01-31.

Datatype.Name: data
Datatype.Description: Raw data with no format or content restrictions. Data fields are always immediately preceded by a length field. The length field should specify the number of bytes of the value of the data field (up to but not including the terminating SOH). Caution: the value of one of these fields may contain the delimiter (SOH) character. Note that the value specified for this field should be followed by the delimiter (SOH) character as all fields are terminated with an "SOH".

Datatype.Name: MonthYear
Datatype.Description: char field representing month of a year in YYYYMM format. Valid values: YYYY = 0000-9999, MM = 01-12.

Datatype.Name: DayOfMonth
Datatype.Description: int field representing a day during a particular monthy (values 1 to 31).

Fields.Name: Account
Fields.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between broker and institution.

Fields.Name: AdvId
Fields.Description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: AdvRefID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: AdvSide
Fields.Description: Broker's side of advertised trade

Fields.Name: AdvTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

Fields.Name: AvgPx
Fields.Description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

Fields.Name: BeginSeqNo
Fields.Description: Message sequence number of first record in range to be resent

Fields.Name: BeginString
Fields.Description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Fields.Name: BodyLength
Fields.Description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Fields.Name: CheckSum
Fields.Description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Appendix B for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN RECORD; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-record delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

Fields.Name: ClOrdID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which electronically submit multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ClOrdID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Fields.Name: Commission
Fields.Description: Commission. Note if CommType is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

Fields.Name: CommType
Fields.Description: Commission type

Fields.Name: CumQty
Fields.Description: Total number of shares filled.

Fields.Name: Currency
Fields.Description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See Appendix A for information on obtaining valid values.

Fields.Name: EndSeqNo
Fields.Description: Message sequence number of last record in range to be resent. If request is for a single record BeginSeqNo = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "999999"

Fields.Name: ExecID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by broker (will be 0 (zero) for ExecTransType=3 (Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: ExecInst
Fields.Description: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Fields.Name: ExecRefID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier used with Cancel and Correct transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: ExecTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies transaction type

Fields.Name: HandlInst
Fields.Description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

Fields.Name: IDSource
Fields.Description: Identifies class of alternative SecurityID

Fields.Name: IOIid
Fields.Description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: IOIOthSvc
Fields.Description: Indicates if, and on which other services, the indication has been advertised. Each character represents an additional service (e.g. if on Bridge and Autex, field = BA, if only on Autex, field = A)

Fields.Name: IOIQltyInd
Fields.Description: Relative quality of indication

Fields.Name: IOIRefID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: IOIShares
Fields.Description: Number of shares in numeric or relative size.

Fields.Name: IOITransType
Fields.Description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

Fields.Name: LastCapacity
Fields.Description: Broker capacity in order execution

Fields.Name: LastMkt
Fields.Description: Market of execution for last fill Valid values: See Appendix C

Fields.Name: LastPx
Fields.Description: Price of this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType = 3 (Status)

Fields.Name: LastShares
Fields.Description: Quantity of shares bought/sold on this (last) fill. Field not required for ExecTransType = 3 (Status)

Fields.Name: LinesOfText
Fields.Description: Identifies number of lines of text body

Fields.Name: MsgSeqNum
Fields.Description: Integer message sequence number.

Fields.Name: MsgType
Fields.Description: Defines message type. ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U1, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver.

Fields.Name: NewSeqNo
Fields.Description: New sequence number Valid values: 0 - 999999

Fields.Name: OrderID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by broker. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Fields.Name: OrderQty
Fields.Description: Number of shares ordered

Fields.Name: OrdStatus
Fields.Description: Identifies current status of order.

Fields.Name: OrdType
Fields.Description: Order type.

Fields.Name: OrigClOrdID
Fields.Description: ClOrdID of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

Fields.Name: OrigTime
Fields.Description: Time of message origination (always expressed in GMT)

Fields.Name: PossDupFlag
Fields.Description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

Fields.Name: Price
Fields.Description: Price per share

Fields.Name: RefSeqNum
Fields.Description: Reference message sequence number

Fields.Name: RelatdSym
Fields.Description: Symbol of issue related to story. Can be repeated within message to identify multiple companies.

Fields.Name: Rule80A
Fields.Description: Note that the name of this field is changing to "OrderCapacity" as Rule80A is a very US market-specific term. Other world markets need to convey similar information, however, often a subset of the US values. . See the "Rule80A (aka OrderCapacity) Usage by Market" appendix for market-specific usage of this field.

Fields.Name: SecurityID
Fields.Description: CUSIP or other alternate security identifier

Fields.Name: SenderCompID
Fields.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

Fields.Name: SenderSubID
Fields.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

Fields.Name: SendingTime
Fields.Description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in GMT)

Fields.Name: Shares
Fields.Description: Number of shares

Fields.Name: Side
Fields.Description: Side of order

Fields.Name: Symbol
Fields.Description: Ticker symbol

Fields.Name: TargetCompID
Fields.Description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

Fields.Name: TargetSubID
Fields.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

Fields.Name: Text
Fields.Description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

Fields.Name: TimeInForce

Fields.Name: TransactTime
Fields.Description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in GMT)

Fields.Name: Urgency
Fields.Description: Urgency flag

Fields.Name: ValidUntilTime
Fields.Description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in GMT)

Fields.Name: SettlmntTyp
Fields.Description: Indicates order settlement period. Absence of this field is interpreted as Regular. Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution.

Fields.Name: FutSettDate
Fields.Description: Specific date of trade settlement in YYYYMMDD format. Required when SettlmntTyp = 6 (Future) or SettlmntTyp = 8 (Sellers Option). (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

Fields.Name: SymbolSfx
Fields.Description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Absence of this field indicates common. Valid values: As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory

Fields.Name: ListID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Fields.Name: ListSeqNo
Fields.Description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of ListNoOrds, 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

Fields.Name: ListNoOrds
Fields.Description: Total number of orders within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of ListNoOrds, e.g. 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

Fields.Name: ListExecInst

Fields.Name: AllocID
Fields.Description: Unique identifier for allocation record. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: AllocTransType
Fields.Description: Identifies allocation transaction type

Fields.Name: RefAllocID
Fields.Description: Reference identifier to be used with Replace and Cancel AllocTransType records. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Fields.Name: NoOrders
Fields.Description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

Fields.Name: AvgPrxPrecision
Fields.Description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

Fields.Name: TradeDate
Fields.Description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this record in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

Fields.Name: ExecBroker

Fields.Name: OpenClose

Fields.Name: NoAllocs

Fields.Name: AllocAccount

Fields.Name: ProcessCode

Fields.Name: RptSeq

Fields.Name: CxlQty

Fields.Name: AllocStatus

Fields.Name: AllocRejCode

Fields.Name: Signature

Fields.Name: SecureDataLen

Fields.Name: SecureData

Fields.Name: BrokerOfCredit

Fields.Name: SignatureLength

Fields.Name: EmailType

Fields.Name: RawDataLength

Fields.Name: RawData

Fields.Name: PossResend

Fields.Name: EncryptMethod

Fields.Name: IOIQualifier

Fields.Name: WaveNo

Fields.Name: Issuer

Fields.Name: SecurityDesc

Fields.Name: HeartBtInt
Fields.Description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

Fields.Name: ClientID

Fields.Name: MinQty
Fields.Description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed.

Fields.Name: MaxFloor
Fields.Description: Maximum number of shares within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time.

Fields.Name: TestReqID
Fields.Description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

Fields.Name: ReportToExch

Fields.Name: LocateReqd

Fields.Name: OnBehalfOfCompID

Fields.Name: OnBehalfOfSubID

Fields.Name: QuoteID

Fields.Name: NetMoney

Fields.Name: SettlCurrAmt

Fields.Name: ExpireTime

Fields.Name: DKReason

Fields.Name: DeliverToCompID

Fields.Name: QuoteReqID

Fields.Name: OfferPx

Fields.Name: BidSize

Fields.Name: OfferSize

Fields.Name: DeliverToLocationID

Message.Name: Heartbeat
Message.Description: The Heartbeat monitors the status of the communication link and identifies when the last of a string of messages was not received.

Message.Name: TestRequest
Message.Description: The test request message forces a heartbeat from the opposing application.

Message.Name: ResendRequest
Message.Description: The resend request is sent by the receiving application to initiate the retransmission of messages. This function is utilized if a sequence number gap is detected, if the receiving application lost a message, or as a function of the initialization process.

Message.Name: Reject
Message.Description: The reject message should be issued when a message is received but cannot be passed through to the application level.

Message.Name: SequenceReset
Message.Description: The sequence reset message is used by the sending application to reset the incoming sequence number on the opposing side.

Message.Name: Logout
Message.Description: The logout message initiates or confirms the termination of a FIX session.

Message.Name: IOI
Message.Description: Indication of interest messages market merchandise which the broker is buying or selling in either a proprietary or agency capacity.

Message.Name: Advertisement
Message.Description: Advertisement messages are used to announce completed transactions.

Message.Name: ExecutionReport
Message.Description: The execution report message is used to: 1. Confirm the receipt of an order 2. Confirm changes to an existing order (i.e. accept cancel and replace requests) 3. Relay order status information 4. Relay fill information on working orders 5. Reject orders 6. Report post-trade fees calculations associated with a trade

Message.Name: OrderCancelReject
Message.Description: The order cancel reject message is issued by the broker upon receipt of a cancel request or cancel/replace request message which cannot be honored.

Message.Name: Logon
Message.Description: The logon message authenticates a user establishing a connection to a remote system.

Message.Name: News
Message.Description: The news message is a general free format message between the broker and institution.

Message.Name: Email
Message.Description: The email message is similar to the format and purpose of to the News message, however, it is intended for private use between two parties.

Message.Name: OrderSingle
Message.Description: The new order message type is used by institutions wishing to electronically submit securities and forex orders to a broker for execution.

Message.Name: OrderList
Message.Description: The new order list message type is used by institutions wishing to electronically submit lists of related orders to a broker for execution.

Message.Name: OrderCancelRequest
Message.Description: The order cancel request message requests the cancellation of all of the remaining quantity of an existing order.

Message.Name: OrderCancelReplaceRequest
Message.Description: The order cancel/replace request is used to change the parameters of an existing order.

Message.Name: OrderStatusRequest
Message.Description: The order status request message is used by the institution to generate an order status message back from the broker.

Message.Name: Allocation
Message.Description: The allocation record instructs a broker on how to allocate executed shares to sub-accounts.

Message.Name: ListCancelRequest
Message.Description: The list cancel request message type is used by institutions wishing to cancel previously submitted lists either before or during execution.

Message.Name: ListExecute
Message.Description: The list execute message type is used by institutions to instruct the broker to begin execution of a previously submitted list.

Message.Name: ListStatusRequest
Message.Description: The list status request message type is used by institutions to instruct the broker to generate status messages for a list.

Message.Name: ListStatus
Message.Description: The list status message is issued as the response to a List Status Request message and indicates the current state of the orders within the list as they exists at the broker's site.

Message.Name: AllocationInstructionAck
Message.Description: The allocation ACK record is used by the broker to acknowledge the receipt and status of an allocation record received from the institution.

Message.Name: DontKnowTrade
Message.Description: The Don’t Know Trade (DK) message notifies a trading partner that an electronically received execution has been rejected.

Message.Name: QuoteRequest
Message.Description: In some markets it is the practice to request quotes from brokers prior to placement of an order. The quote request message is used for this purpose.

Message.Name: Quote
Message.Description: The quote message is used as the response to a Quote Request message and can be used to publish unsolicited quotes.

Message.Name: SettlementInstructions
Message.Description: The Settlement Instructions message provides either the broker’s or the institution’s instructions for trade settlement.
